text:
{'text': 'We ordered a takeaway meal for an early Mother‚Äôs Day celebration at home, and everything lived up to expectations. Have been supporting Beng Hiang since its Amoy Street days, and I‚Äôm happy that the quality remains just as I remember from the good old times.

The portions were decent, packaging was neat, and cutlery was included for takeaway. We went with our all-time favourites of mixed prawn rolls, oyster omelette, braised pork with buns, and seafood noodles.

The flavours were classic and definitely old-school, which makes it perfect for the older generation, though perhaps less suited to younger palates.

Recommended for family gatherings with the elderly!', 'languageCode': 'en'}
